@startuml
title IAM Anomaly Detection Pipeline

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam ArrowColor #4C78A8
skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #4C78A8
  BackgroundColor #EAF2F8
}

rectangle "CERT Activity Datasets\n• device.csv\n• logon.csv\n• file.csv" as data

rectangle "Data Loading\n• Load each CSV\n• Standardise column names\n• Validate required fields\n• Merge by date" as load

rectangle "Data Cleaning\n• Remove duplicates\n• Handle missing values\n• Convert dates and booleans\n• Standardise categories" as clean

rectangle "Feature Engineering\n• Time and weekend features\n• After-hours activity\n• User/device/file counts\n• USB activity and session density" as features

rectangle "Preprocessing\n• Label-encode user, PC, activity\n• Create preview/correlation charts\n• Standardise all features" as prep

rectangle "Training Sample\nUp to 10,000 rows" as sample

rectangle "Isolation Forest\nTree-based isolation\nProduces labels and anomaly scores" as iforest #D5F5E3
rectangle "Local Outlier Factor\nLocal density comparison\nProduces labels and anomaly scores" as lof #D5F5E3
rectangle "Autoencoder\nNeural reconstruction model\nUses reconstruction-error threshold" as ae #D5F5E3

rectangle "Evaluation and Comparison\n• Anomaly totals\n• Training time\n• Consensus-based comparison\n• User/device/activity insights" as evaluation #FCF3CF

rectangle "Saved Outputs\nTables: feature matrix, predictions, scores, summary\nModels: scaler and trained models\nReports: execution and model comparison\nFigures: charts and visualisations" as outputs #FDEDEC

data --> load
load --> clean
clean --> features
features --> prep
prep --> sample

sample --> iforest
sample --> lof
sample --> ae

iforest --> evaluation
lof --> evaluation
ae --> evaluation
evaluation --> outputs

note right of evaluation
  Unsupervised setting:
  no ground-truth labels are required.
  Models are compared using anomaly
  counts, scores, runtime, and agreement.
end note

@enduml
